Threads Supplemental Privacy Policy

Copy link

Effective January 21, 2026

Threads is provided by Meta Platforms Ireland Limited ("Meta", "we", "our" or "us") and is built by Instagram. With a Threads Account, you can share, view, and interact with content on the Threads app and website (Threads). Your use of Threads is governed by the Threads Terms of Use.
Threads integrates with third party services (Third Party Services) via an interoperable protocol, and is part of a network sometimes called the Fediverse. In the Fediverse, Threads users can share content with, view and interact with content from, follow, and be followed by people outside of Threads who use such Third Party Services (Third Party Users). To enable these interactions between Threads users and Third Party Users we share information about Threads users with Third Party Services, and collect and process information about Third Party Users, even if they dont have an account on Threads or other Meta Products as described further below.
At present, Threads is not interoperable with Third Party Services, and well update this note, when interoperability is ready. As such, information in this Threads Supplemental Privacy Policy describing what information we collect and how we use and share it when Threads is interoperable with Third Party Services, is not yet applicable.
The Meta Privacy Policy describes the information we process to support the Meta Products, including Threads. This Threads Supplemental Privacy Policy supplements the Meta Privacy Policy by providing a detailed overview of the information that we collect, process and share to support Threads. It also describes how we collect, process and share information when Third Party Users interact with Threads and when Threads users interact with Third Party Users.
You can find links to helpful sections of the Meta Privacy Policy below, but we encourage you to also read all of the Meta Privacy Policy to learn more about the information we collect, and how we use and share it on Meta Products. In addition, please see the Meta Cookies Policy for information regarding our use of cookies and other similar technologies.

What information do we collect?

The Meta Privacy Policy describes the information we collect under What information do we collect?. Below, please find additional detail regarding information we collect when you use or interact with Threads:
  • Your Threads activity and information that you provide:

    We collect information you provide to us when you use or interact with Threads, including:
    • Threads Profile Information: We collect the information you provide when you create your Threads profile, including your name, email address, and settings and preferences.
    • Threads Activity: When you use Threads, we collect information about your activity on Threads, including the content you create, the types of content you view or interact with and how you interact with it, metadata about your content, the Threads features you use and how you use them, the hashtags you use, and the time, frequency, and duration of your activities on Threads. Learn more about activity information in the Meta Privacy Policy.
    • Threads Followers and Other Connections: We collect information about followers, and other users and communities youre connected to and interact with.
  • App, browser, and device information: We collect and receive information from and about the different devices you use and how you use them, as further described in the Meta Privacy Policy. Learn more about how we use cookies and similar technologies in the Meta Cookies Policy.
  • Information we collect from Third Party Services and Third Party Users: We collect information about the Third Party Services and Third Party Users who interact with Threads. If you interact with Threads through a Third Party Service (such as by following Threads users, interacting with Threads content, or by allowing Threads users to follow you or interact with your content), we collect information about your third-party account and profile (such as your username, profile picture, and the name and IP address of the Third Party Service on which you are registered), your content (such as when you allow Threads users to follow, like, reshare, or have mentions in your posts), and your interactions (such as when you follow, like, reshare, or have mentions in Threads posts).

How do we use this information?

We use the Threads information we collect for Threads for the purposes described in the Meta Privacy Policy under How do we use your information?, including:
  • to provide, personalise (including ads if we show you ads), and improve Threads,
  • to provide measurement, analytics and other business services,
  • to promote safety, integrity and security across Meta Products,
  • to communicate with you, and
  • to research and innovate for social good.
Threads in Accounts Centre: You can choose to add your Threads account to an Accounts Centre with other Meta Company Products accounts. If you do so, we will use your information across these accounts as described here.

How is information shared?

In addition to sharing information in the ways described in the Meta Privacy Policy under How is your information shared on Meta Products or with integrated partners?, How do we share information with third parties? and How do the Meta Companies work together?, Threads information is shared in the following ways when you use Threads with a profile:
  • Public Information: Some of your information on Threads is always public and available to anyone, on or off Meta Products, including your username, name, profile picture, and bio. For content you share, you can set the audience by choosing between a private or public profile. With a private profile, only followers you approve can see and interact with the content you share. If your profile is public, anyone on or off Threads can see and interact with the content you share, including on Third Party Services (see below) and other Meta Products like Facebook. You can also restrict the audience for your content by blocking individual accounts from viewing them. Keep in mind that whether your profile is private or public, some information on your profile, such as your username, name, profile picture, and bio remain public. Learn more about how you can control your Threads profile privacy.
  • Sharing With Third-Party Services & Users: Threads is integrated with Third Party Services via an interoperable protocol. This means that you can use Threads to share content with Third Party Users via their respective Third Party Service, such as by making your profile public or by approving followers from Third Party Services. It also means that you can interact with content and people from these Third Party Services, without having to leave Threads. When you interact with content or Third Party Users or otherwise make your content available to Third Party Services, e.g. by having a public profile, please be aware that you are directing us to deliver your information to services not controlled by Meta as necessary to integrate with the interoperable protocol, so that your information can be stored and processed by the Third Party Services, and be surfaced to their Third Party Users.
    • For example, when you have a follower who is a Third Party User, we will share a copy of your post and your information to this followers Third Party Service so that it can store, process, and deliver the post to your follower. Similarly, if you make your profile public, a copy of your post and your information is made available to the applicable Third Party Service so that it can store and process that information.
    • As another example, when you like or reply to a post from a Third Party Service, you are asking us to share a copy of that like or reply to the Third Party Service so that it can be stored, processed, and delivered to the user and appear along with the post. Well receive similar information from the Third Party Service so that you can see the post and its comments.
    • The information we share with the Third Party Service will depend on your activity, but usually will include your profile information (such as your username, name, profile picture, and bio), and could also include things like the content of the comment, interaction, or post, including any attachments such as photos or videos; and certain metadata associated with your interaction, such as IP address of our Threads server and the timestamp of the interaction.
     Threads is interoperable with Third Party Services, so keep in mind that, because of Threads integration with Third Party Services, content you share is not limited to Meta and Threads users. Information sent to Third Party Services is no longer in Metas control and is subject to the terms and policies of those Third Party Services. People in your audience, including Third Party Users, can view your content and can choose to share it with others outside your audience.
Similarly, we collect and process information from Third Party Services and Third Party Users to show this information on Threads when Third Party Users interact with or allow interactions from Threads, e.g. by approving Threads users among their followers, replying or otherwise interacting with posts and content from Threads users, or by making information publicly available via their Third Party Service.

What is our legal basis for processing your information and what are your rights?

When you use Threads, we process the information as described above, including your Threads Profile Information, Threads Activity, Threads Followers and Other Connections, as described in the Meta Privacy Policy:
  • as necessary to fulfil the Threads Terms of Use and the Instagram Terms of Use, including to provide the Threads experience and to enable interoperability with Third Party Services and Third Party Users (once Threads is interoperable with Third Party Services);
  • consistent with your consent, which you may revoke at any time;
  • as necessary to comply with our legal obligations;
  • to protect your vital interests, or those of others;
  • as necessary in the public interest; and
  • as necessary for our (or others') legitimate interests, unless those interests are overridden by your interests or fundamental rights and freedoms that require protection of personal data.
Learn more about these legal bases and how they relate to the ways in which we process data.
For Threads users under the age of majority (under 18, in most applicable countries) who have a limited ability to enter into an enforceable contract only, where we may be unable to process your information on the grounds of contractual necessity as described above, we rely on our legitimate interests or the legitimate interests of a third party, where they are not outweighed by your interests or fundamental rights and freedoms. The categories of information we use, the legitimate interests relied on and why and how its processed are set out in the Meta Privacy Policy.

Exercising your rights

We offer you a variety of tools to view, manage, download, and delete your Threads information by visiting your Threads Settings. You can also learn how to exercise your rights including how to access, correct, port, and delete your information by visiting our Help Center, your settings for Threads, and your device-based settings. You can delete your Threads account at any time. Learn more about deleting your Threads account in our Help Centre. You can also contact Meta to exercise your rights.

How long do we keep your information?

We keep information as long as we need it to provide our Products, comply with legal obligations, or protect our or other's interests. We decide how long we need information on a case-by-case basis. Learn more about how we decide how long to keep information in Metas Privacy Policy.

Further information and how to contact Meta with questions

The data controller responsible for your personal data is Meta Platforms Ireland Limited, which you can contact online or via the contact address below at:
